72
00:09:27,393 --> 00:09:33,299
Always remember not to forget.
A child's dream is a dream they
should never get.

73
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:43,944
[laughing]

74
00:09:45,912 --> 00:09:48,715
You look beautiful as ever,
Queen Nehalennia.

75
00:09:49,215 --> 00:09:50,050
[screams]

76
00:09:51,417 --> 00:09:54,154
How may I be of service, my
beautiful Queen?

77
00:09:54,555 --> 00:09:55,956
[screams]

78
00:09:57,157 --> 00:10:02,669
[screams]

79
00:10:08,374 --> 00:10:12,045
<i>(Queen Nehalennia) I discovered</i>
<i>that by devouring the dreams of</i>
<i>others...</i>

80
00:10:12,178 --> 00:10:15,849
<i>I could retain eternal youth</i>
<i>and everlasting beauty.</i>

81
00:10:16,182 --> 00:10:18,351
<i>I could gain immortality.</i>

82
00:10:18,418 --> 00:10:23,690
<i>And so, I devoured the dreams of</i>
<i>every one of my retainers and</i>
<i>subjects.</i>

83
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:28,729
<i>I decided to live my life</i>
<i>alone...</i>

84
00:10:28,862 --> 00:10:34,067
<i>with none to keep me company but</i>
<i>the animated corpses of my</i>
<i>retainers.</i>

85
00:10:44,144 --> 00:10:47,914
Tell me, do you know why this
place is rising?

86
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:48,915
Huh?

87
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:52,719
Forces have been set in motion
to seal me up again.

88
00:10:52,886 --> 00:10:57,390
<i>(Queen Nehalennia) In the</i>
<i>darkness of the New Moon, back</i>
<i>inside the mirror.</i>

89
00:11:00,226 --> 00:11:05,071
So be it. I don't want a future
in which I bear this hideous
form.

90
00:11:05,271 --> 00:11:09,075
Inside the mirror I can be
beautiful forever.

91
00:11:09,309 --> 00:11:11,745
But you'll also be alone
forever.

92
00:11:11,912 --> 00:11:15,415
Silence! What would you know?!

93
00:11:15,516 --> 00:11:17,183
[grunts]

94
00:11:17,818 --> 00:11:26,793
[grunting]

95
00:11:28,028 --> 00:11:32,298
My revenge for your stealing my
beauty, is your death!

96
00:11:32,465 --> 00:11:39,105
[laughing]

97
00:11:39,973 --> 00:11:46,212
[grunting]

98
00:11:46,312 --> 00:11:47,948
I feel sorry for you!

99
00:11:48,014 --> 00:11:49,015
Huh?

100
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:51,484
[sighs]

101
00:11:54,555 --> 00:11:59,125
[painful breaths]

102
00:11:59,325 --> 00:12:03,136
Don't look at me that way! You
looked at me just like that...

103
00:12:03,637 --> 00:12:06,139
Right before I was sealed in the
mirror!

104
00:12:06,907 --> 00:12:08,141
What do you mean?

105
00:12:08,208 --> 00:12:10,343
Stop giving me that look of
pity!

106
00:12:10,476 --> 00:12:14,515
I don't want pity or sympathy!
Not from you!

107
00:12:14,648 --> 00:12:15,916
Not from you!

108
00:12:16,016 --> 00:12:16,983
[gasps]

109
00:12:21,021 --> 00:12:22,989
Stop. What are you doing?

110
00:12:23,056 --> 00:12:26,993
You people took away from me
that thing I cherished most of
all.

111
00:12:27,994 --> 00:12:32,365
Well now I'm going to return the
favor by taking away what you
cherish most!

112
00:12:34,434 --> 00:12:35,836
[gasps]

113
00:12:38,438 --> 00:12:39,339
[gasps]

114
00:12:41,041 --> 00:12:43,009
Chibi Moon!

115
00:13:16,249 --> 00:13:17,217
[gasps]

116
00:13:18,952 --> 00:13:20,621
Chibi Moon!

117
00:13:30,263 --> 00:13:34,100
[gasping]

118
00:13:34,234 --> 00:13:35,401
No...

119
00:13:37,070 --> 00:13:43,143
[chuckling] How does it feel,
losing someone you love? Losing
your happy future?

120
00:13:43,309 --> 00:13:46,412
Now you know the despair I felt.

121
00:13:46,513 --> 00:13:47,247
[gasps]

122
00:13:48,114 --> 00:13:49,249
<i>(Queen Nehalennia) What are you</i>
<i>doing?</i>

123
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:52,252
I won't give up! I'm not like
you!

124
00:14:04,104 --> 00:14:05,271
The fool.

125
00:14:06,707 --> 00:14:10,343
She's thrown away her dreams and
her future for someone that she
loves.

126
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:17,217
<i>(Queen Nehalennia) And so it</i>
<i>begins. My time alone.</i>

127
00:14:21,688 --> 00:14:26,459
[chuckles] I'm not letting go of
my dream.

128
00:14:26,627 --> 00:14:30,330
And I will never become an
adult, never!

129
00:14:33,466 --> 00:14:39,239
Always remember not to forget. A
child's dream is a dream they
should never get.

130
00:14:44,244 --> 00:14:47,213
Fine, then! I will continue to
live alone!

131
00:14:47,648 --> 00:14:50,050
All alone.

132
00:14:51,417 --> 00:14:55,989
But I will be young and
beautiful forever!

133
00:14:59,259 --> 00:15:03,269
[laughing]

134
00:15:57,157 --> 00:15:58,391
Chibi Moon!

135
00:16:10,844 --> 00:16:13,079
<i>The wind's carrying her away</i>
<i>from me!</i>

136
00:16:23,123 --> 00:16:25,626
<i>It's no use! I'll never catch</i>
<i>up!</i>

137
00:16:35,769 --> 00:16:39,640
<i>No. I can do it! I have to do</i>
<i>it! I'll never give up!</i>

138
00:17:21,655 --> 00:17:24,591
[light gasping]

139
00:17:28,662 --> 00:17:29,896
[grunts]

140
00:17:32,666 --> 00:17:37,904
Chibi Moon! You have to wake up!
I can't use the power of the
Golden Crystal by myself!

141
00:17:40,206 --> 00:17:41,675
[gasps]

142
00:17:43,744 --> 00:17:49,716
[gasps] Chibi‐Usa! You have to
wake up. Open your eyes!
Chibi‐Usa!

143
00:17:56,790 --> 00:17:59,726
Come on, Chibi‐Usa! You've...

144
00:18:00,627 --> 00:18:02,736
If you don't wake up, we'll die.

145
00:18:04,437 --> 00:18:06,573
We won't live to see our future!

146
00:18:07,908 --> 00:18:10,711
Chibi‐Usa. Please open your
eyes.

147
00:18:14,247 --> 00:18:18,719
We're meant to grow up together,
to become adults together!

148
00:18:18,885 --> 00:18:22,556
So we can make our dreams come
true!

149
00:18:25,826 --> 00:18:27,728
[grunts]

150
00:18:27,828 --> 00:18:28,729
[gasps]

151
00:18:28,829 --> 00:18:31,397
You're right, Sailor Moon.

152
00:18:31,632 --> 00:18:35,235
We need to make our
dreams come true.

153
00:18:35,301 --> 00:18:36,937
Chibi‐Usa!

154
00:18:43,910 --> 00:18:47,681
She's calling me...my young
maiden.

155
00:19:36,903 --> 00:19:38,805
Do you really have to go?

156
00:19:38,905 --> 00:19:41,474
Just when we were finally
getting to know you.

157
00:19:41,575 --> 00:19:44,845
There's an empty room at our
shrine that you'd be more than
welcome to stay in.

158
00:19:44,978 --> 00:19:50,551
Thank you. But I'm afraid I
can't remain in your world much
longer now that peace has come.

159
00:19:50,651 --> 00:19:54,855
I must return to the sacred land
of Elysion to protect the Golden
Crystal.

160
00:19:55,088 --> 00:19:56,857
Aw, that's too bad.

161
00:19:58,358 --> 00:20:03,269
My Prince, Princess, it's thanks
to you that I was able to
fulfill my duty.

162
00:20:04,771 --> 00:20:06,540
We should be thanking you.

163
00:20:06,607 --> 00:20:08,008
It was you who saved this world.

164
00:20:08,108 --> 00:20:10,276
<i>(Mamoru) And me.</i>

165
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:13,346
He's right. For a moment I
thought we were done for.

166
00:20:13,446 --> 00:20:15,015
Yeah, you can say that again.

167
00:20:15,115 --> 00:20:17,851
Come on, Chibi‐Usa! Stop being
shy all of the sudden!

168
00:20:17,951 --> 00:20:20,954
Hey, let go! And I'm not being
shy.

169
00:20:22,488 --> 00:20:24,390
Chibi‐Usa, may I?

170
00:20:24,725 --> 00:20:26,392
[gasps]

171
00:20:31,497 --> 00:20:32,666
No way!

172
00:20:32,799 --> 00:20:34,300
Now even Chibi‐Usa...

173
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,637
Has gone and beat us to the
punch.

174
00:20:38,572 --> 00:20:41,742
My young maiden...I'll never
forget you.

175
00:20:42,075 --> 00:20:43,877
Same here.

176
00:20:43,977 --> 00:20:45,979
Hmm?

177
00:20:46,046 --> 00:20:47,881
<i>(Ves‐Ves) Uh look! A UFO!</i>

178
00:20:47,981 --> 00:20:49,883
What? Where? I don't see it!

179
00:20:50,751 --> 00:20:52,418
[sighs]

180
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:58,925
There, you see? I'm still
capable of a little magic even
without my orb.

181
00:20:59,025 --> 00:21:01,034
Well, should we get going then?

182
00:21:01,167 --> 00:21:04,905
What? Without even saying
goodbye to everyone?

183
00:21:05,005 --> 00:21:08,341
Sad farewells are
definitely not our thing.

184
00:21:08,408 --> 00:21:11,678
Don't worry. I'm sure we'll be
seeing them all again someday.

185
00:21:26,727 --> 00:21:28,394
Pegasus!

186
00:21:30,564 --> 00:21:35,035
Farewell, young maiden. I can't
thank you enough for everything
you've done for me.

187
00:21:35,602 --> 00:21:39,706
Wait, Pegasus, wait! Please
don't go yet!

188
00:21:41,975 --> 00:21:42,909
[heavy breathing]

189
00:21:49,482 --> 00:21:56,089
I never got a chance to tell you
anything. I never even told you
what my dreams are.

190
00:21:56,222 --> 00:21:57,090
<i>(Usagi) [soothing sigh]</i>

191
00:21:57,223 --> 00:21:58,625
[gasps]

192
00:21:58,725 --> 00:22:00,901
I'm sure you'll
see him again.

193
00:22:01,902 --> 00:22:04,671
Mhm! You're right.

194
00:22:05,739 --> 00:22:09,075
<i>(Chibi‐Usa) Yes. I'm sure we</i>
<i>will meet again.</i>

195
00:22:09,142 --> 00:22:13,914
<i>And when we do, I'm going to</i>
<i>tell him all about my dream.</i>

196
00:23:53,219 --> 00:23:56,189
<i>(Queen Nehalennia) How the</i>
<i>flames of my hatred still burn!</i>

197
00:23:56,289 --> 00:23:58,191
<i>(Usagi) Nehalennia? But how?</i>

198
00:23:59,793 --> 00:24:01,802
<i>(Queen Nehalennia) Now that I've</i>
<i>returned you don't stand a</i>
<i>chance against me!</i>

199
00:24:01,902 --> 00:24:04,204
<i>Not even your new allies can</i>
<i>save you!</i>

200
00:24:04,270 --> 00:24:08,709
<i>(Usagi) New allies? [gasps] Is</i>
<i>that? Haruka! And Michiru, too!</i>

201
00:24:08,775 --> 00:24:14,981
<i>Next time on Sailor Stars: "The</i>
<i>Flower of Nightmares Scatters:</i>
<i>The Queen of Darkness Returns."</i>

202
00:24:15,081 --> 00:24:17,918
<i>The moonlight is a messenger of</i>
<i>love.</i>

